sentence: 1 -RRB- Voters can `` buy `` one of two brands when they select their political agents -- a Republican brand that believes in the minimalist state and in the virtues of private markets over the vices of public action , and a Democratic brand that believes in big government and in public intervention to remedy the excesses attendant to the pursuit of private interest .
mut.sentence: Voters can `` buy `` one of two brands when they select their political agents -- a Republican brand that believes in the minimalist state and in the virtues of private markets over the biggest vices of public action , and a Democratic brand that believes in the biggest government and in public intervention to remedy the excesses attendant to the pursuit of private interest .
reason: 原句中的'big government'指的是较大规模的政府干预，而变异句中的'the biggest government'含义更偏向于强调政府干预的最大化，这里的用法带有比较级，使得政府角色的强调有所不同，因此两个句子的目标词含义存在差异。
